pr_review_comment_body:
You should make serial_settings default to None and then do:

```
if serial_settings is None:
    serial_settings = {}
```

Otherwise you run into an issue with Python mutables (i.e. we would get some unwanted side-effects).

I think we should only fill in output shape dim size when the corresponding input shape dim size is non-zero.
That is if input shape is (0, 20), begin=(0, 0), end=(5, 10), it should return (0, 10), instead of (5, 10) as inferred output shape.
@sandeep-krishnamurthy Could you confirm?

nit: avoid `\`. Use `()`.

    from tchannel.tornado.message_factory import (
        build_inbound_request_cont,
        build_inbound_request
    )

